                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On stray stones on the roof of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Maṅgaḷapurīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Jaṭāvarmaṉ Sundarapāṇḍya.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The date portion in this inscription is lost. Palaeographically it may be assigned to the 13th century A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This record registers a gift of land to a temple for the expenses of worship and offerings on the new moon and full moon days (<hi rend="italic">uvāppaḍi</hi>) by Sāriputra Paṇḍitaṉ Mention is also made of the <hi rend="italic">Saṅgattār</hi> of the place.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
